messages.text_en:
🇪🇺 EU military products are entering Russia through Turkey and China.  
🖥 According to a study by ifo Institute and EconPol Europe, despite EU sanctions, military goods from Europe continue to be imported into Russia via third countries. Turkey serves as the main hub for this trade.  
💼 Key figures from the report:  
🛑 Turkey – 36% (more than half of the indirect exports);  
🛑 China – 23% (almost a quarter);  
🛑 Hong Kong – 16%;  
🛑 UAE – 10%.  
💭 “Since the beginning of 2024, the EU has significantly increased and expanded its restrictions on exports to Russia. As a result, there are fewer instances of sanctions being circumvented through third countries. However, sanctioned military goods from the EU still make their way into Russia through these channels,” says ifo trade expert Theodora Teti.  
ℹ️ According to researchers, these export restrictions have only increased Russia’s costs of purchasing these goods by 19%. The authors note that these figures are just “the lower limit,” and the actual amount may be much higher.  
