 ➡️ About €400 million will fund the purchase and transfer of the Tridon Mk2 air defense systems — Swedish-made systems particularly effective against Russian drone swarms. It involves sensors, robots, hunting drones and even anti-aircraft guns. Everything will be vehicle-mounted. Sweden will also supply sensors, robotic systems, and anti-aircraft guns;

 ➡️ €524 million will support Ukrainian production of long-range missiles and drones, both in the air and on the water;

 ➡️ The remaining over €280 million will cover grenade launchers from Swedish army stocks, as well as artillery shells, spare parts, and training for Ukrainian personnel. 

 ❗️ The total volume of Sweden’s military assistance to Ukraine since February 2022 has already exceeded $9 billion

